name: Loblaws City Market Arbutus
address: Loblaws City Market Arbutus, 3185 Arbutus St, Vancouver, BC V6J 3Z3

detailed_reviews.review_text: I am glad to have a grocery store nearby that opens from 7am to 11pm. It was a brand new store when they opened in 2015. Friendly staff especially Monika and Dawn. Large underground parking or park along Arbutus St after 7pm. I am glad that you dont need any coins for their shopping carts.

Very very clean and tidy and staff are on the ball even when just opening super friendly does not judge and they give a sense being welcomed in the store nice and calm easy to navigate and everything looks fresh i would dare say this is by far the cleanest and most welcoming loblaws in all of b.c koodos to management at this location stellar job

Pretty good deals, decent variety and has a couple of actual Mexican products (La Costena beans and adobo, Mexican Coca-Cola, charras Tostadas). Also have some tomatillos (green tomatoes) and chiles (Serrano, Poblano, etc). Check them out in the photos!

I like this store in my neighborhood, especially the small cafe inside. The store is spacious and well organized, clean, and carries a lot of products. The meat and seafood are always fresh. I d like to get my yoghurt and oat milk here, of which they have many varieties and at reasonable prices. I used to come daily  to their cafe for fresh made breakfast sandwiches and coffee before COVID. Today, I came again. And Marla  at the counter was very patient to customize my breakfast sandwich. Although it was busy, she still came to ask the customers how their breakfasts were. I highly recommend this store, especially their breakfast sandwiches and coffee.

Nice supermarket. Prices are good, but some things are strange crazy overpriced, like some sausages for 25 per package, the same exact pac in Safeway is only 5. The same time some milk twice cheaper, buying all the time. Great parking, using all the time, one of reason why coming.

Its nice   local store for the area  . Its owned by loblaws so its a  high end fancier version of no frills  .   They have a awsome cake area here .   It has a  underground parking lot and its next to the Arbutus greenway and the  #33 & #16   busses  stops here
We ordered a full sheet birthday cake - strawberry shortcake - the cake was amazing - thanks to the bakery department

Great local, very nice store, parking and good price points, staff are very nice. If you go in later they have half priced meals and sandwiches. Not huge but does the trick in our community and so much better than the IGA!!
One of the best grocery store around. Well supplied. Staff is extremely helpful and will go above and beyond to help you find what you need.
An extremely helpful staff. They even helped  me to get to the correct side of the checkout. You will understand what this means if you go to the store a little inside  joke.
One of the best food stores in Vancouver, amazing selection of cheeses, ready to go meals and an outstanding butchery. No complaints whatsoever!
Clean store with a large variety of produce. Their chopped vegetables salad collection is very comprehensive compared to other convenient stores, and i always came here to buy those.

Excellent customer service.  Al the staff are extremely professional, customer service oriented and genuinely friendly. A very well managed and run store.  As outstanding as all the staff are I have to say how great Marco is.  He went above and beyond the service he provided not only to me but also to an elderly woman who required additional assistance. Marco is truly a rare find in todays commercial establishments.  Thank you.
Very good and delicious food and excellent service. I really appreciate and recommend this place.
Nice shop near the bike trail. Perfect place for a break!

Even though I live close by, I rather go to Safeway .  I don t know why but I do.  Tonight I decided to come here to Grab a few things.  I got great service from Chase who worked in the bakery dept.  he went out of his way to help me find items and he actually sent me in the wrong direction for something but made the effort to comeback to find me and send me in the right direction which saved me time.  Total appreciate it as that s what I would have done.  I ll definitely start shopping here more often .  Thanks Chase !
Great selection and found these fresh chicken wings for 10.99 for 16 pieces... Pizza party here we come
I love their cheese selection and the prices.

Great customer service! My go-to place for Island Farms ice cream as it carries the coolest flavours that other stores don t. Thank you for always checking stock for me over the phone before I head over.
Great parking and they have good sushi too.
Awesome and friendly service. Very knowledgeable staff
Great variety of food ready to eat as well as groceries at good prices.

a great little market with a variety of mainstream and upscale offerings. seemingly always stocked well. if you need only a few items or a whole grocery list with household items, youll definitely find it here!

This grocery store is located on the site of the previous Ridge theatre. There is now a grocery store with condominium complex located on top of it. It is a fantastic location right on the arbutus Ridge at the intersection of king Edward and arbutus. The store itself is not the largest loblaws that you will encounter however certainly is pretty full service. The produce is fresh which is a good sign for any type of grocery store. Theres lots of prepared foods here as well and just about anything you could find at a typical loblaws actually. There is pretty good street parking outside and I did not try the underground parking today. Theres lots of bicycle parking out front as well. And they have a large selection of plants for sale outside as well. This was our first time in the store and wanted to see if it would become our staple for groceries as we have just moved into the area. Its a really great location and value for money is good. Will certainly come again and probably very frequently.
I love this Loblaws and I especially love when the Dr Oetker pizzas go on sale. You should totally try them!

I ve been ordering my groceries for pick up since the beginning of coronavirus. It s a great service that never disappoints me. Quality produce, realistic prices and SO convenient for someone like me who doesn t particularly enjoy walking the aisles of a grocery store. I ve been inside there one time tho.. and it s exceptionally clean and absolutely beautiful! But nonetheless I prefer driving into the parking lot and having my groceries loaded into my trunk. Thank you Loblaws!

Free parking underground and free street parking. Groceries are all reasonably priced and competitive compared to other places. Fruits and vegetables are very fresh. Good mix of staple items as well specialty items. Staff is friendly. Self checkout works well.

Good selection for a smallish grocery store. I like getting steaks and poultry at this location. I wish they would carry more pork options other than just ground pork and boneless pork chops. Again, I am all about proper social distancing protocols right now and I feel at ease shopping here. Plenty of free underground parking available but could get bottleneck if you have to wait for bad drivers and inconsiderate people that take their time putting groceries in their cars.
Monica is great great special quality of food excellent

The staff very friendly and helpful. The store was very organized and very clean. The shelves were very well stocked and the prices I cant complain. I enjoyed my shopping experience and I highly recommend it to anyone who wants to save money and have friendly people who are willing to lend an extra pair of hands

Great store, excellent prices and great location. Ive always found everything that I need in here and the staff is very helpful in case you may need some help finding something and even on costumer service they are quite nice

Although the prices are on the $$ side, they do have a good number of items on sale! This place is still cheaper than a few other grocery stores near the university. Make sure to try out the in-store baked muffins and cakes. Theyre really good! Also their vegetables are fresh.
This store has a really good selection of grocery items and they are reasonably priced.
I teach Argentine Tango and as a dance instructor I need to eat healthy. This is a great store and price are not bad. I like this place. Also has easy parking.

I really enjoy shopping here. Atmosphere is excellent and there s always sale items that make it into my weekly meal prep. The cashiers are Also friendly and the store layout mostly makes sense. 10/10

This store has the best customer service Ive ever encountered! And its not just a few people, it is almost every single employee. When I asked if they had a certain Presidents Choice brand product they didnt just say an aisle number & send me on my way; they actually took me right to the item. And on another occasion where we couldnt find the item anywhere in the store after looking together for 10 minutes, the staff member found his store manager (who was the most knowledgeable about which items are stocked & which have been discontinued). And when the store manager said they didnt carry it, he then proceeded to look up which Presidents Choice type stores (No Frills, City Market, Your Independent Grocer, T&T Supermarket, etc) in Vancouver had it in stock & then wrote down the address on a piece of paper for me & verbally gave me directions to the store. Now *thats* what I call customer service! This City Market also carries a wide variety of higher end items such as an entire wall of specialty cheeses from around the world, artisanal marinated meats & sausages, Presidents Choice brand products not available at any of the other PC stores, artisanal salsas & many other artisanal & high end products. I highly recommend this City Market location. As with most grocery stores today, this location is wheelchair accessible, has wheelchair parking, underground parking accessible from the alley, those half-sized shopping carts that are free (in addition to full-sized grocery carts & carrying baskets) & is open til 11pm (which is great for night owls).

Great bakery, well run Syrus is great, the muffins nice and the halla bread soft and delicious. Long ago had a mexican chocolate cake deep chocolate with a spicy hint it was delicious. Love the cheese selection, and fresh made sushi. Its even got my friends dogs special treats. Good selection helpful staff.
I had a great experience at the location. They have a good range of meat and bakery stuff. Manager named Shiwani was so helpful, she was so professional but with a good humour.
Ryan in management took good care off me today. I appreciate that. Thanks Ryan!

This is a really beautiful market grocery store. Its more of a Whole Foods than regular grocery store, but the prices are more in line with normal human stores. Id love it if there was outdoor parking, but the parkade is free, and the selection of custom sausages and deli meats, fine cheeses, and fresh-made products will bring me back over competitors.

Nicest grocery pickup that Ive ever visited. In-store the employees are very friendly and helpful. Great experience shopping in the environment. Food is good. Highly recommended for groceries and delicious ready-to-eat meals.

Michelle at Arbutus City market needs to recognized. Amazing customer service. Friendly, efficient and so helpful.  Not sure if she takes a day off? As a high risk family, she sees that all our needs are met for safe pickup. Amazing
Very friendly staff. Prices are reasonable.
Well kept grocery store and always freshly stocked. Decent sales and perks especially if you have the Optimum card. Store size is nice too as it avoids being oversized like the usual supercenters.
Great neighborhood supermarket for its size. Excellent butcher, cheese and deli sections. Decent fruits and vegetables. Too bad not bigger.

Overall it is a fairly decent shopping experience. Some great value items are mixed in with some more expensive stuff. You can shop here on any budget. The cheese selection is quite good for a grocery store.
Fantastic but more expensive than superstore. But fresh and quality produce. They even hang their own dry aged beef. Great selection of cheeses, bread and fresh baked sweets.

My family drove by here on the way to a craigslisters house. After we came back to City Market. WOW! 2nd time back here and it still amazes me how beautiful this place looks. I dont care about prices here because this is the rich end of town. They have extensive ready made foods, cool deli (hams hanging and aging), bakery (open concept oven), butcher (meats aging) and even a coffee bar with ice cream. Everybody can complain about service and prices in their review. But really? There are more people working in here than a big Superstore. Try going to a No Frills or an Independent and compare. Prices are cheaper there but you wont get the cool stuff here. Must visit this store at least once to see what a grocery store looks like on the rich side of the city.
Very good grocery market

The cake baker did an amazing job of the cowboy boots my mom wanted on her birthday cake. I think it was the bakers assistant too! Have yet to taste it but if its anything like their other baked goods , I know it will be delicious.
It is a very clean and bright store. The staff are lovely and it wasnt busy. Would definitely go back there to shop for sale items.

Fresh and ready food to eat for on the go. Loved when they would 50% off stuff almost expiring me and my bf would go crazy in there when they had the richmond location. It didnt last long. so I was pretty disappointed when it closed down. Sometimes wed even get their inhouse made cheese pizza and then grab our own deli meat and veggies and create our own pizza. There needs to be more of this store. For real. This place had everything.
Good pre-made meals

Great customer service, prices and sales are better than most. Bright, clean, and good flow. The only thing that is confusing is the checkout area. (Im told theyre working on the issue) I love this store!

Smaller Loblaws grocery store with a boutique feel. Has a mix of higher end items and good Presidents choice products. Had lots of fun using the self serve bread slicing machine. It even lets you choose the slice thickness.

Loblaws has made a great effort to bring a great market experience with quality products to Vancouvers west side. I like shopping there because of their friendly staff and they cater to your any need. Their deli and meat departments staff are great and make an effort to remember you.

Nice place to shop! lovely variety to pick from, also alot of healthy choices to pick from. And yummy food to eat there is you ever feel hungry while shopping.  Enjoyable experience. About the same prices as other places.

This a great place for breakfast while you come to shop around for groceries. My partner and I were going for a nice walk earlier today, and he got very hungry. We decided to stop somewhere nice for breakfast, but we decided to scramble into the first place we saw (partner getting a bit hangry)! So we stumbled across Loblaws. We stopped by at the little cute cafe in the back of the store with plenty of seating. Here we found a nice selection of gelato, assortment of coffees, bakery buns, and ofcourse, breakfast sandwiches. Although, they only had the breakfast sandwich on the menu as the only option for breakfast, we looked no further into buying one. My partner ordered a very nice Americano and two of the breakfast sandwiches, and I ordered one. The breakfast sandwiches were only 3.99 each (served on your choice of brioche, croissant or bagel) with grilled bacon, American cheese and an egg with lettuce and tomato. It kept us full and it definitely satisfied my partners tummy. The girls working here are also delightful and give you a good portion! We will be returning!!:)

This is the best store Ive ever been into. Think Presidents Choice, but the throw in the most amazing decor, and wonderful staff. I spent almost 30 mins just chatting about cheese in the deli one afternoon!
Bright cheerful clean store.  Wide variety of foods and lots of choice.  Good prices.

This is the first Loblaws City Market in Vancouver and is a great alternative to Whole Foods. The layout is a little tricky compared to larger grocery stores but worth checking out if you wish Whole Foods and Superstore had a baby. The fresh-pressed juices and impressive cheese selection might be worth a visit alone.

One of the better supermarkets in Point Grey.  Great selection of fresh produce and meats as well as a good selection of prepared food.  Give up on trying to use the underground parking and just park on a side-street and walk.  Lavazza coffee and Ice Cream in the north-east corner...

I love this new location, it is beautiful, has a fair selection of products, and I can use my PC points here. Very happy theyve opened this store up so close to home, so I dont have to go all the way down to superstore (the no frills in Kits is terrible, I wont go there).

This place is clean, well played out, easy to get into and out of isles. Everything is orderly and well maintained. The staff is friendly and helpful but not ever in your face. Great experience each time I have visited.
Im a major fan of this store. High quality foods, good pricing, large selection, and merchandised very well. I wish they had one closer to downtown Vancouver. Id do all my grocery shopping there.
The location is beautiful as well as the store itself. Good variety of meat products and bakery stuff, friendly staff specially the girl who helped me, Shiwani.
Very nice inner city grocery store. Lots of local products.
16th.  & Arbutus --  Convenient location with polite,  personable and  knowledgeable staff. My go to grocery store with competitive prices.
Fresh food. Excellent quality. Great service.
This place is AMAZING. Incredible array of stuff and so clean!! The cleanest and nicest smelling public washroom Ive ever been in. Hahaha. The staff are lovely too. Great spot.
Nice store layout. Enjoyable shopping experience.
Nice little community grocery store. For a small space they carry an unexpected variety of food items. Friendly staff.
Best deli. Pretty good selection despite being the most expensive grocery store besides Choices and Whole Foods.   Shoppers not physically distancing and no enforcement.
Great location, staff is amazing (even with the wild craziness thats going on) the store was doing its best to stock shelves with what they had and what was out was still organized and well presented
Wide variety of products. Fresh fruits and veggies. Comfortable place to shop. Love the weekly discounts and other special promotions
Great store. Walked in mid evening to find a sewing kit. Took me less than a minute to find on my own. Staff are friendly and check out was quick
Shopping at this location was very relaxing and enjoyable. The cashier she was happy and professional at her job. Thank you for the great shopping experience. I will return to this location.

This is a great grocery store and we love it for both in-store shopping and PC Express pick-up. We ve found some great items there, like a PC branded non-alcoholic lemon radler (it s addictively good)
Love this store. Awesome staff and the bakery is my favorite place to go. Amazing cakes and cant beat the price.
Pretty nice grocery store with decent prices. Has a good selection of cheese and took COVID seriously. Would recommend to a friend.
Good, high quality food. Staff leave you alone and give you space. This is my go to grocer.

Great place to have ur groceries from ( compared ro save on foods at ubc area). Plenty of variety, clean, and not crowded when i went there. Definatly going back there again. And it is bigger than what you see from outside
Convenient location, good quality produce and a comfortable shopping experience. One of my go-to grocery stores in the city!
Fantastic place for not just grocery shopping but has its own coffee shop and the best deli for hot meals in the area. Gotta try it out.
Great store with beautiful and a variety of product. Ready made meals and easy parking.
Good and friendly staff here. No complaints here.
Possibly the best place I have ever been too. I go at least twice a day and the staff and products are top notch. If I could it ten stars I would.
They have an excellent selection of natural and organic foods without the insane prices of other organic grocery chains such as $4 for a muffin.
Love service,especially my favourite S A beautiful older cashier who makes me laugh & great converse. I do love this place.
Like any other grocery store but have a good cheese and dry aged meat section. Worth taking a look if you like those things.
We love this location! Always clean and well loaded up with fresh groceries. Very friendly stuff!
I really like the vibe here. Great selection of Presidents choice brand items. Even more awesome theyre open late, till 11pm
Great place, fresh produce, large product variety and very friendly staff, excellent shopping experience overall
Has everything you need and more for fairly decent prices! Really good selection of a wide variety of foods, and the prepared food section is great.
We just stopped by really quick on Wednesday. But it looks clean and staff is friendly and helpful.
Love this shop, a little more expensive than other stores however they have a great selection and the staff are amazing
Easy parking.  Self check outs. Picked up organic eggs and  ethical spinach for my health guru teenage daughter
Love the shopping here. Great selection and everything is very fresh. Not a lot of lineups either
Fantastic store with a lot of fresh produce, good price and clean store
This is a beautiful grocery store. Very clean and well stocked. The staff are very friendly

name: Loblaw Pharmacy
address: Loblaw Pharmacy, 350 SE Marine Dr, Vancouver, BC V5X 2S5

detailed_reviews.review_text: Pharmacy manager goes beyond to provide exceptional service. Phone in automated refill service is great. Some of the pharmacy technicians could use some customer service retraining or learn to experience some empathy. Try not to go during peak business hours, lines ups will be long. The wait for prescriptions will be approximately 45 mins - 1 hour. Do your grocery shopping while you wait.

April update: the staff are great. I see them hustle every time I get medication filled. They are understaffed and overworked but do their best to help. Any issues I ve had in the past are out of their control.
Manager is handsome and helpful. Staff are kind.

I always get my medication here and I never had any problems. Often times the medication is ready later than stated, but they do seem very busy all the time. I feel like everyone is working hard, they may just be a bit understaffed, hence the delays.
Very nice staff, its my go to for medication needs.  Doris is the best !
This is a good supper store One of the better ones The staff are good And they always have what you are looking for
Staff is always helpful
Love it, very convenient
Nice
Ive only had great experiences with this place... Except one time they couldnt figure out how to charge my insurance place in person (we figured it out over the phone later that day)
Friendly pharmacist and alot quicker then most pharmacys

I see other peoples reviews here saying its not a great place- but I would disagree. The wait time when I come in on a friday and saturday has not been bad at all, and the staff are friendly and knowledgeable. I mean, its a simple clinic inside a superstore, you already dont want to be there when youre in there, but its not as bad as everyone has been saying, in my experience anyway
They always get it right and theyre a compounding pharmacy. However, their waits are very long.
Wonderful people and great service
Good price
Clinic and pharmacy pharmacy
They sell all kinds of medicines

Located inside the Real Canadian Super Store inset off of Marine Dr near Main Str in South Vancouver. There can be a bit of a wait to fill your prescription. But the staff is friendly & knowledgeable. And the  pharmacy is  well stocked bright and clean. Flu shot are also available here. The best part is you can do all your grocery shopping here while they fill the prescription. And lots of free parking .
Customer service is poor . If you call them to ask for particular medicine they always say we dont have this med. .
Good prices...pharmacists are great...the assistants are hit and miss
So so pharmacy.
Good drug store

Dropped off my prescription at 5pm today and was told that it will be ready in 1 hour, so I leave and come back at 6:30pm because I know their estimate is never right. I go up to the counter to pick up my medication and they tell me to wait on the side for 5 minutes and pointed towards the medication information corner. I wait in the medication information corner for about 40 minutes while they process 10 other people who received and paid for medications. The person who initially told me to wait for 5 minutes left to go for her break and did not tell anyone about my prescription. I went to line up again for the prescription pickup line and they just took it from the counter and gave it to me. I dont understand why the person who went for their break did not just process my prescription when it was already ready and on the counter.

I dont want to be rude and I dont usually like to leave negative reviews but this place is very... Challenging, Ill say. I havent had much of a problem at the counter or with wait times, but the first few times I filled a prescription they kept forgetting or failing to bill my extended benefits. Annoying but not awful. My biggest challenge is refills. The phone number currently printed on the bottles is incorrect. The phone number listed on Google is also wrong. Even the automated system you get when you call Superstore sends you to the wrong number. I had to get someone at the customer service desk to tell me the number, hang up, and redial it directly. I picked this pharmacy because I recently moved nearby and I usually get my groceries at Superstore, so this seemed like an easy decision. How could it be less convenient than driving 25 minutes across town to my old pharmacy near my old apartment? Superstore accepted my challenge and exceeded my expectations.

Generally poor service.  Prescription isnt always ready when automated telephone refill time says it will.  Have refilled a prescription 3 months in a row and every time they didnt have enough stock to fill it - hello - you have a customer with refills on the prescription you should know that they are coming back to refill in a month and get some stock in!!  Also shortened the hours on stat holidays without posting it on the website so I went without meds another time.  I have switched to another pharmacy.
I tried to drop off prescribed mouth wash which I got from them before. The lady saw the paper and gave me a very rude attitude telling me they dont carry it.
Dont sell high quality product

Save yourself some stress by going to a different pharmacy! I should have checked the google reviews before wasting my time. ALL the pharmacy staff in this location is a joke. No regard for privacy, they look like they don t know what they re doing, doesn t communicate properly and looks like they don t want to be there to do a proper job! What a shame, such unprofessional team.

Very very disappointed with staff. I went to pharmacy today around 11:30am and there was long line ups and i understand they were busy. However, the female pharmacist she looks very tired with no smile at all and she looks like she doesnt care at all. Also, there was another asian female staff at pick up prescription area and she was super rude. I didnt understand what she told me was and i asked same question twice and suddenly both of staff(female pharmacist and pick up area staff) they were laughing in front of me which is ridiculous and very rude. This pharmacy needs to re-train your staff there, all the staff there was super rude and they need to learn how to greet customer and also need to learn how to smile at customer. I will never visit this pharmacy never again!! very unprofessional
Stay away! Such Unprofessionals are working there. 1, super long wait time. 2, poor communication 3, Big mistake, I found someones durg in my receipt bag. Please find a better pharmacy and stay safe.

Its my first time to go this pharmacy and it was terrible.  When I drop my prescription, Darison helped me but she was very rude and disrespect the customer. She think queen of the pharmacy or something. And she told me will be ready after 35min then when I pick up my staff they are not ready. I was waiting extra 1 hour..... Can you please hire good manger here?

I have not felt inclined to leave a google review until now because of how BAD my experience was today. I called them before going there, and they told me they had enough stock to give me two refills and that it would be 40 minutes. In previous times I have gone, they have taken longer than they said they would, so this time I came after 50 minutes instead of 40 to give them more time. When I arrived they made me wait ANOTHER 20 MINUTES! I ended up waiting DOUBLE the time they estimated. When they finally called me to the counter they informed me that they were 6 pills short and that I would need to come back in THREE DAYS to get them! A few of the staff members are rude as well. Especially a short-haired blonde woman who might be a supervisor, Im not sure. She seems to have no empathy whatsoever.

Very rude and indifferent Pharmacy staff. I went in to pick up an RX, which I dropped off several days prior. They had to order the medication and told me it would be available in 2 days. To be sure, I went to pick it up 5 days later. The rude staff member then told me  oh we  didnt order it, check back later. Excuse me but I do have a life outside of constantly running in and out of a  pharmacy to pick up my now week  old RX! It would have nice if she offered an apology for my inconvenience, or asked if Id be interested in delivery to save me a 3rd trip into the store, but the only sound that came out of her mouth was next, clearly indicating that she couldnt care less about the customers she is paid to serve, and hated her job.

Went to get prescription eye drops for my eye that was swelling a little bit. I asked the lady receptionist how much it will cost approximately and the lady couldnt answer because she cant remember the price off the top of her head and brushed it off. Alright, she was a little rude, but okay. 30+ minutes later I came back to pick it up. I was supposed to receive 5ml of the solution, but was given 10ml. I did research after that to find out that the company manufacturing the solution either stopped or did not manufacture the 5ml solution. I understand that its not the pharmacys fault, but I just find it unfair to be charged for a higher dosage than what I was anticipating and prescribed and not be told about it when picking it up. Only to find out when getting home.

Every time I have been to this pharmacy the wait times have been unbelievable. I understand there are lots of orders to fill but if they know they are never going to fill the prescription in a said amount of time so why do they continue to tell everyone an unrealistic wait time. 35 minutes is alot of time to wait in the first place but when almost every persons wait time is double that.....STOP TELLING PEOPLE YOULL BE DONE IN 35 MINUTES!!!! If you would just tell people come back in an hour, then maybe youd have enough time to do the orders and your reviews wouldnt be so terrible.

Prices are good but the service is terrible. They were supposed to renew my prescription one month ago and didnt follow up. It is the pharmacys responsibility to follow-up and ensure the fax gets to the Dr. They never followed up. Im out of my prescription and they are not doing a very good job of following up now. What do I do without my prescription? Go blind?!?! I need my eye drops!!!! They told me to relax. Condescending and rude is what that is.

The service is really bad and one of their staff is super rude, unbelievable. I dont know her name, but she is a girl with short hair and usually stand in the drop off prescription area. The story is I got the prescription from the doctor, and my insurance benefit can cover 100% my bill with the prescription. When I showed my insurance benefit card, she was impatient and said you should give me earlier. Why she didnt ask me earlier? That is okay, after she said this medicine cant be covered by my insurance. I said it is impossible because my insurance cover 100% medicine with prescription. She became very impatient and rude, and said you should check your insurance first, then come. I was really annoyed why I should check first? If I check, how I can know which prescription that doctor will provide me? After she asked me to go to another counter to pay the money in full, she left without any words. It is very horrible service and I feel really uncomfortable. I dont mind If I cant get covered by insurance, but she should treat customer with basic respect, not challenge and rude all the time. I still remember last time I was there and drop off my prescription, and asked her some questions, and she was very impatient as well.  I wont go to this pharmacy anymore, never!!!

I would have arrived a few minutes before their 8pm closing to get a flu shot, but I was turned away on the phone and told to return tomorrow. I arrived anyway and parked with 4m before closing. I thought the flu shot was at the upstairs medical clinic so I climbed those stairs. After seeing those doors closed, I realized it must be at the inside store pharmacy. When I reached the pharmacy, it was still before 8pm, but it looked like it was closed already. I called my brother to check other pharmacies still open and was told of a competitor nearby thats open till 12am. So Im going there now to get my flu shot instead.

WORST PHARMACY - I dont think I have ever had a good experience here and that is in all honesty. Every single time I come here (and I dont know why I keep coming back, this pharmacy messes up my prescriptions, my orders, everything). Today my doctor called in my prescription at 3PM and they said they had no record of it. Every time I order something, they never have it on time or they never call me. They are rude, they are not helpful and they have very poor customer service.

Last summer,  I asked the pharmacy to order for me an unavailable prescription drug and one of the staff said it should be ready in 5 days.  After five days I went back it wasnt there yet.  So another order was placed according to the staff.  A week later I came back and it still wasnt there.  Turned out nobody from the staff was placing the order.  Complained this to the management, that was all thats needed for the pharmacy staff to go into action of finally ordering the meds.  Some of the drugstore staff have very mean attitudes, though some are okay.  Dont go there to buy prescription, buy them somewhere else.

I am not racist but I called today and this indian lady who answered my call was in a hurry and she answered me we dont have that ok?
